Tactic.Ring.evalConstMul","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Ring.html#Tactic.Ring.evalConstMul","doc":"Evaluate `k * a` where `k` is a rational numeral and `a` is in normal form. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Ring.lean#L242-L245","name":"Tactic.Ring.horner_mul_const","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Ring.html#Tactic.Ring.horner_mul_const","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Ring.lean#L237-L240","name":"Tactic.Ring.horner_const_mul","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Ring.html#Tactic.Ring.horner_const_mul","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Ring.lean#L181-L234","name":"Tactic.Ring.evalAdd","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Ring.html#Tactic.Ring.evalAdd","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Ring.lean#L174-L179","name":"Tactic.Ring.horner_add_horner_eq","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Ring.html#Tactic.Ring.horner_add_horner_eq","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Ring.lean#L167-L172","name":"Tactic.Ring.horner_add_horner_gt","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Ring.html#Tactic.Ring.horner_add_horner_gt","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Ring.lean#L160-L165","name":"Tactic.Ring.horner_add_horner_lt","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Ring.html#Tactic.Ring.horner_add_horner_lt","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Ring.lean#L155-L158","name":"Tactic.Ring.horner_add_const","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Ring.html#Tactic.Ring.horner_add_const","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Ring.lean#L150-L153","name":"Tactic.Ring.const_add_horner","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Ring.html#Tactic.Ring.const_add_horner","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Ring.lean#L136-L147","name":"Tactic.Ring.evalHorner","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Ring.html#Tactic.Ring.evalHorner","doc":"Evaluate `horner a n x b` where `a` and `b` are already in normal form. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Ring.lean#L130-L133","name":"Tactic.Ring.horner_horner","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Ring.html#Tactic.Ring.horner_horner","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Ring.lean#L126-L128","name":"Tactic.Ring.zero_horner","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Ring.html#Tactic.Ring.zero_horner","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Ring.lean#L114-L120","name":"Tactic.Ring.HornerExpr.pp","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Ring.html#Tactic.Ring.HornerExpr.pp","doc":"Pretty printer for `horner_expr`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Ring.lean#L111-L111","name":"Tactic.Ring.HornerExpr.reflConv","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Ring.html#Tactic.Ring.HornerExpr.reflConv","doc":"Reflexivity conversion for a `HornerExpr`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Ring.lean#L107-L108","name":"Tactic.Ring.HornerExpr.xadd'","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Ring.html#Tactic.Ring.HornerExpr.xadd'","doc":"Construct a `xadd` node "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Ring.lean#L102-L104","name":"Tactic.Ring.HornerExpr.isZero","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Ring.html#Tactic.Ring.HornerExpr.isZero","doc":"Is this expr the constant `0`? "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Ring.lean#L99-L99","name":"Tactic.Ring.HornerExpr.instCoeHornerExprExpr","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Ring.html#Tactic.Ring.HornerExpr.instCoeHornerExprExpr","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Ring.lean#L95-L97","name":"Tactic.Ring.HornerExpr.e","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Ring.html#Tactic.Ring.HornerExpr.e","doc":"Get the expression corresponding to a `HornerExpr`. This can be calculated recursively from\nthe structure, but we cache the exprs in all subterms so that this function can be computed in\nconstant time. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Ring.lean#L88-L88","name":"Tactic.Ring.instInhabitedHornerExpr","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Ring.html#Tactic.Ring.instInhabitedHornerExpr","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Ring.lean#L84-L86","name":"Tactic.Ring.HornerExpr","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Ring.html#Tactic.Ring.HornerExpr","doc":"Every expression in the language of commutative semirings can be viewed as a sum of monomials,\nwhere each monomial is a product of powers of atoms. We fix a global order on atoms (up to\ndefinitional equality), and then separate the terms according to their smallest atom. So the top\nlevel expression is `a * x^n + b` where `x` is the smallest atom and `n > 0` is a numeral, and\n`n` is maximal (so `a` contains at least one monomial not containing an `x`), and `b` contains no\nmonomials with an `x` (hence all atoms in `b` are larger than `x`).\n\nIf there is no `x` satisfying these constraints, then the expression must be a numeral. Even though\nwe are working over rings, we allow rational constants when these can be interpreted in the ring,\nso we can solve problems like `x / 3 = 1 / 3 * x` even though these are not technically in the\nlanguage of rings.\n\nThese constraints ensure that there is a unique normal form for each ring expression, and so the\nalgorithm is simply to calculate the normal form of each side and compare for equality.\n\nTo allow us to efficiently pattern match on normal forms, we maintain this inductive type that\nholds a normalized expression together with its structure. All the `Expr`s in this type could be\nremoved without loss of information, and conversely the `horner_expr` structure and the `ℕ` and\n`ℚ` values can be recovered from the top level `Expr`, but we keep both in order to keep proof\nproducing normalization functions efficient. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Ring.lean#L62-L62","name":"Tactic.Ring.horner","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Ring.html#Tactic.Ring.horner","doc":"The normal form that `ring` uses is mediated by the function `horner a x n b := a * x ^ n + b`.\nThe reason we use a definition rather than the (more readable) expression on the right is because\nthis expression contains a number of typeclass arguments in different positions, while `horner`\ncontains only one `CommSemiring` instance at the top level. See also `HornerExpr` for a\ndescription of normal form. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Ring.lean#L48-L55","name":"Tactic.Ring.addAtom","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Ring.html#Tactic.Ring.addAtom","doc":"Get the index corresponding to an atomic expression, if it has already been encountered, or\nput it in the list of atoms and return the new index, otherwise. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Ring.lean#L42-L44","name":"Tactic.Ring.mkAppCS","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Ring.html#Tactic.Ring.mkAppCS","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Ring.lean#L37-L40","name":"Tactic.Ring.RingM.run","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Ring.html#Tactic.Ring.RingM.run","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Ring.lean#L35-L35","name":"Tactic.Ring.RingM","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Ring.html#Tactic.Ring.RingM","doc":"The monad that `ring` works in. This is a reader monad containing a cache and\nthe list of atoms-up-to-defeq encountered thus far, used for atom sorting. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Ring.lean#L31-L31","name":"Tactic.Ring.State.numAtoms","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Ring.html#Tactic.Ring.State.numAtoms","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Ring.lean#L28-L29","name":"Tactic.Ring.State","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Ring.html#Tactic.Ring.State","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Ring.lean#L23-L26","name":"Tactic.Ring.Cache","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Ring.html#Tactic.Ring.Cache","doc":"This cache contains data required by the `ring` tactic during execution. "}]}